@David__Osland Who’s Next ahead of Quadrophenia.

Magazine’s The Correct Use of Soap is still magnificent.

Several of the Talking Heads albums—the post-post punk ones—stand up well. I’d probably call out Remain In Light.

@five_books Greetings From Bury Park, by Sarfraz Mansoor. 
Memoir of a Springsteen-obsessed Anglo-Pakistani boy growing up in Luton in the 1980s. 
(Enjoyed the film adaptation that they made, Blinded by the Light.)

@SuzanneEvans1 From the 2019 Conservative Manifesto:

“We will lead the global fight against climate change by delivering on our world-leading target of Net Zero greenhouse gas emissions by 2050, as advised by the independent Committee on Climate Change.”

You could have Googled this.

In #JustTwoThings today—using ‘seeds of change’ as a #visioning tool. And flying cars are coming—if they can work out where to land and take off from. 
